name: Seasons in the Park
description: Elevated Pacific Northwest dishes served in a park setting, with panoramic views of the city.
address: Seasons in the Park, W 33rd Ave, Vancouver, BC V5Y 2M4

featured_reviews.review_id: While the food was average, the breathtaking view and reasonable prices made it a worthwhile experience. The menu offered a variety of dishes, but they lacked that special something to make them truly memorable. However, the real star of the show was the panoramic view of the surrounding landscape. Watching the view while enjoying a reasonably priced meal was a delightful experience. If you're looking for a budget-friendly dining option with a stunning view, this place is worth a visit.

featured_reviews.review_id: We had our wedding reception brunch of about 60 people in the Skyline Room at Seasons in the Park restaurant in early August of 2023, and we were blown away by the outstanding service at our wedding! The food was delicious, the portions were generous, and the restaurant was more than happy to accommodate a few of our guests who had dietary restrictions. The service was fast, and the communication with us was incredible. So many of our guests also complimented the excellent service they received during our reception, and we had so many compliments about the beautiful view of Vancouver as well. The servers even went out of their way to ensure that we, the bride and groom, were comfortable and well taken care of during the entire brunch. Even the preplanning was smooth and seamless, and communicating back and forth with Makda about wedding details was an easy process. Many of our guests have commented that this was one of the best weddings they've been to, and we could not have done it without all the wonderful help provided by Seasons. As a wedding venue, we highly recommend Seasons in the Park! Plus, we felt compared to other wedding venues, that Seasons was quite reasonable, and who can beat that beautiful view of Vancouver, and wonderful setting within Queen Elizabeth Park. Thank you very much Seasons for making our special day so wonderful!

featured_reviews.review_id:
Pleasantly surprised at the quality and value-for-money here.  Got the 3 course lunch menu and left very satisfied.

The steak was tender and flavorful.  The cake was quite substantial and rich.  The creme brulee had hints of citrus in it.

The mushroom soup was lacking a bit tho.  A bit bland, had to add some more salt and pepper to it myself but couldn't really help it.

Service was very good and the views are amazing on the patio.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Seasons in the Park gave my girlfriend and I an excellent dining experience for our date night. Neither of us had been here before and we were both very impressed with the views, food and the service. Our server was amazing and insisted to take photos of us during the sunset, which was such a nice touch to the experience.

We will definitely be coming back here again in the future. I highly recommend anyone come here for dinner and try to get a table on the patio by the fire place, it was absolutely splendid.

featured_reviews.review_id:
We went to this restaurant for a family celebration:

The location was gorgeous, it is a very beautiful restaurant. You can't beat the view. The food was excellent, I would dare to say I chose probably the strongest pick on the menu  The halibut.

Desserts weren't impressive, but they were good.

They didn't get 5 stars based on service. The hostess was not very warm and at any point she didn't say please or thank you.

Our server was ok, he asked if there was a celebration and he brought a dessert on the house, it was nice.

I would still recommend this restaurant, it is a beautiful location and food was great to excellent. Not to mention the beautiful park beside it!

featured_reviews.review_id: Really great meal for both of us (prime rib for me, only available on Sunday suppers). Nice view looking over downtown Vancouver in the distance, and pretty quiet sitting outside. Wait staff was very nice. Did have a very minor issue that I wouldn't have been surprised if anyone as busy as they were at the time would make so they gave us a free (and very good) dessert to make up for it.

featured_reviews.review_id:
One of our dear family friends took me for dinner after a delicate painful sinus procedure I had to fly in from Kelowna.
It's been decades since I have been there, what a beautiful stop to enjoy the view of Vancouver City. Great Service and delicious food. We enjoyed the day's special grilled chard.
We walked away with the sunshine in our pockets, the ultimate healing.

featured_reviews.review_id:
The service was absolutely amazing. Our server and the other staff were attentive without being over bearing. They were really communicative and amazing!

I loved their cocktails, their bread, the Caesar salad and their desserts. The main courses however were things you could find at any other restaurant with the same taste.

The view was outstanding, and you could see the city along with the Queen Elizabeth park. They have heaters in the patio section along with blankets. The restaurant seemed catered to older persons.

Main meals were priced at $20-$40.
